This directory (cw_odmr) is sorta irrelevant (I think). These use the mfli lock-in with photodiode
which isn't really used anymore

in the nv_setup there's an cw_odmr directory with an ODMR measurement file for taking ODMRs with a
single photon counting module (SPCM)

nv_widefield directory is where all code using PCO camera is held, there is the main widefield_odmr
file which takes ODMR of each pixel independently, as well as many debug files which do some binning
or vary a certain parameter taking ODMRs at each point, etc. Most of the code here is copy-pasted
from one another with slight modifications, but where possible I call a pre-defined version of the
function, often in a helper class, to minimize the number of changes required when making modifications.
